snippet.title: Disney REFUSES To Keep Johnny Depp As Jack Sparrow in Pirates of the Caribbean!
snippet.description:
As you all remember, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard‚Äôs divorce has not ended with its finalization back in 2017. As a matter of fact, it‚Äôs continued on up until today, with all the court cases Johnny has filed against Amber‚Äôs team, and even against news outlets, for putting his name on the bad side of the spotlight. When Amber Heard filed for divorce, it did not revolve around your usual divorce cases, it surpassed that and she accused his former husband of hurting her, which Johnny has denied countless times.   And you might think this lost case with a news publisher did not cost him much aside from his reputation, but you‚Äôd be mistaken. When you are a public figure, you need to care A LOT about your image, and for Johnny, this lost case has somehow given other people, especially Amber‚Äôs team, an advantage and a reason for people to believe Amber regarding her allegations. For decades now, Johnny has been considered one of the most versatile actors in the industry, and he seems to still be at the top of his game as he starred in high-grossing films such as Fantastic Beasts and Pirates of the Caribbean, but unfortunately, these roles were cut from him when he lost the libel case against The Sun, as a result of course due to his post-marriage dispute with Amber Heard. 

Following his lost libel case, Johnny Depp was fired from reprising his iconic role as Grindelwald in the critically acclaimed film series Fantastic Beasts. It is no question that the movie series has gained a lot of commercial attention after its initial release. Many fans take a look at Johnny Depp and immediately recognize him as Jack Sparrow, probably his most iconic role yet. People loved Pirates of the Caribbean, specifically, Jack Sparrow, and fans, Disney followers or not, have followed the series from its first movie up until its fifth. And admit it, you just couldn‚Äôt imagine Pirates of the Caribbean without Johnny Depp to play as Jack Sparrow in it. It‚Äôs just absurd to not see him in the franchise. However, sadly enough for fans, the sixth movie of the said series will not be including our favorite Jack Sparrow, much to fans‚Äô dismay. But how did it end up this way? Why won‚Äôt Disney recast Johnny Depp despite Warner Brothers sticking with Amber Heard? Let‚Äôs find out in this video, but before that, make sure to subscribe and hit that notification bell first for more updates. Let‚Äôs dig in!

Pirates of the Caribbean is unarguably one of Disney's most popular, and profitable, live-action franchises that did not stem from a classic animated film, with a multi-billion dollar gross. While the fifth movie in the series, Dead Men Tell No Tales, didn't light up the domestic box office the way previous films did, the movie still made nearly $800 million globally, and that's not the sort of money you would ever expect Disney to just forget about. Now, there have been rumors that there will be a sixth Pirates of the Caribbean movie, however, there are no clear details yet about what this movie will be about. But, despite the vagueness of the details on the next Pirates movie, one thing‚Äôs already for sure‚Ä¶ we won‚Äôt be seeing Johnny Depp as Jack Sparrow. We know what you're thinking, absurd, right? What‚Äôs the point of Pirates of the Caribbean without Johnny Depp? Since he introduced Captain Jack Sparrow to the world, the character and the film series have been one and the same. 

Then there was evidence of her having affairs with an actor and a multi-billionaire, James Franco and Elon Musk. And there was also a phone record where Amber admitted that she hurt him. But what made most people very upset was the fact that Johnny Depp was forced to step down from his roles in Fantastic Beasts, and probably a sixth Pirates movie, while Amber happily and freely trains for her role as Queen Mera in Aquaman 2. 

In 2018, Disney production chief Sean Bailey confirmed that Depp was no longer a part of the Pirates franchise.

It is indeed evident that this saga between Johnny Depp and Amber Heard has caused some riff-raff in his career, as just a few years ago, Johnny was one of the highest-paid actors in the industry, but now, his cases have made him somehow seem less attractive at the box office. But sure enough, if this court case goes well for him and his team, then we hope for sure that he might be able to reprise his roles in Pirates of the Caribbean and even in Fantastic Beasts, if there will be future sequels to come. That‚Äôs all for today, we hope you enjoyed that video and we will see you in the next one. Make sure to like, subscribe, and smash that notification bell for more updates.

"AMBER WON" Amber Heard Feels SHE'S WON and Her Career Is Safe Now | The Gossipy

Amber Heard remains at the frontline of celebrity news due to his ongoing legal battles with ex husband Johnny Depp. The Johnny Depp Amber Heard court case has gotten ugly for many reasons.

With the initial court date being pushed back, Johnny Depp and Amber Heard have been given some more time in order to gather more evidence for their individual cases. For quite some time, the two were firing evidence at each other in order to win in court. 

Ever since the recent release of the footage of the LAPD officers from the penthouse night of Amber Heard and Johnny Depp, things have not been looking all too bright for Amber Heard. Her team has been working tirelessly in order to back up her side, however Johnny Depp seems to have made the attempt to strike back.

snippet.title: Amber Heard [WikiThings EN]
snippet.description:
Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. Born and raised in Texas, she made her film debut in a minor supporting role in the sports drama Friday Night Lights (2004), followed by a series of other small roles in television and film. Her first leading role was in the horror film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), but it was not released in the United States until 2013 due to distribution problems. Her second major role came in the short-running The CW television series Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in the action film Never Back Down and in the stoner comedy Pineapple Express, which were both box office successes. The same year, she received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Heard continued her career with roles in films such as The Informers (2008), The Stepfather (2009), Zombieland (2009), and The Joneses (2009). In 2011, she played the female lead opposite Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and opposite Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary; neither were critically nor commercially successful. Subsequently, Heard appeared in 3 Days to Kill (2014), Magic Mike XXL (2015) and The Danish Girl (2015). She also starred in the indie film The Adderall Diaries (2015), the television musical drama One More Time (2015), and the Martin Amis adaptation London Fields (2018). # Stay Safe.,  # into this together


Music is a powerful art form. While it may get more credit for inspiring people to dance, it also offers a simple way to improve¬†sleep hygiene, improving your ability to fall asleep quickly and feel more rested.

Music can aid sleep by helping you feel relaxed and at ease. With streaming apps and portable speakers, it‚Äôs easier than ever to take advantage of the power of music wherever you go. Given music‚Äôs accessibility and potential sleep benefits, it might be a good time to try adding it to your nightly routine.



Do Binaural Beats Have Health Benefits?



Medically reviewed by¬†Deborah Weatherspoon, Ph.D., R.N., CRNA¬†‚Äî¬†Written by¬†Jacquelyn Cafasso¬†‚Äî¬†Updated on September 18,2018
https://www.healthline.com/health/binaural-beats

What are binaural beats?

When you hear two tones, one in each ear, that are slightly different in frequency, your brain processes a beat at the difference of the frequencies. This is called a binaural beat.

Here‚Äôs an example:

Let‚Äôs say you‚Äôre listening to a sound in your left ear that‚Äôs at a frequency of 132 Hertz (Hz). And in your right ear, you‚Äôre listening to a sound that‚Äôs at a frequency of 121 Hz. Your brain, however, gradually falls into synchrony with the difference ‚Äî or 11 Hz. Instead of hearing two different tones, you instead hear a tone at 11 Hz (in addition to the two tones given to each ear).

Binaural beats are considered auditory illusions. For a binaural beat to work, the two tones have to have frequencies¬†less than 1000 HzTrusted Source, and the difference between the two tones can‚Äôt be more than 30 Hz. The tones also have to be listened to separately, one through each ear. Binaural beats have been explored in music and are sometimes used to help tune instruments, such as pianos and organs. More recently, they have been connected to potential health benefits.

What health benefits are binaural beats claimed to have?

Binaural beats are claimed to induce the same mental state associated with a meditation practice, but much more quickly. In effect, binaural beats are said to:

reduce anxiety

increase focus and concentration

lower stress

increase relaxation

foster positive moods

promote creativity


Binaural beats in the¬†delta¬†(1 to 4 Hz) range¬†ve been associatedTrusted Source¬†with deep sleep and relaxation.

Binaural beats in the¬†theta¬†(4 to 8 Hz) range are linked to REM sleep, reduced anxiety, relaxation, as well as meditative and creative states.

Binaural beats in the¬†alpha¬†frequencies (8 to 13 Hz)¬†are thought to encourageTrusted Source¬†relaxation, promote positivity, and decrease anxiety.

Binaural beats in the lower¬†beta¬†frequencies (14 to 30 Hz)¬†have been linkedTrusted Source¬†to increased concentration and alertness, problem solving, and improved memory.

Find a comfortable place free of distractions. Simply listen to the binaural beat audio for at least 30 minutes each day in your headphones to make sure that the rhythm is entrained (has fallen into synchronization) throughout the brain.

You can experiment with the length of time you listen to the binaural beats to find out what works for you. For example, if you‚Äôre experiencing high levels of anxiety or stress, you may want to listen to the audio for a full hour or longer. Remember, you must use headphones for binaural beats to work. You may also want to listen with your eyes closed
